      <!-- Effects -->
      <div id="effects" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-heading text-navy mb-4">Effects of Higher Differential Speed</h2>
        <p class="text-text-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Higher differential speed reduces the retention time of solids in the decanter bowl. This reduced residence time leads to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-text-light mb-6">
          <li>Higher Solids Output Capacity</li>
          <li>Lower Torque Load On Scroll</li>
          <li>Reduction in Cake Drying Capacity (Wetter Solids)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-text-light leading-relaxed italic mb-6">It is essential to note that the scroll conveying speed should not be higher than that required for satisfactory sludge separation.</p>

        <p class="text-text-light leading-relaxed mb-4">The following chart summarizes the effects of scroll speed on decanter performance.</p>
        <img src="/images/decanter-centrifuge-differential-speed/decanter-differential-speed-effects-400.jpg" alt="Scroll Speed Effects on Decanter Performance chart showing relationship between differential speed, cake dryness, and solids output" width="400" height="286" loading="lazy" class="rounded-lg w-full mb-3" />
