        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-heading text-navy mb-4">Automatic Control of Scroll Speed</h2>
        <p class="text-text-light leading-relaxed mb-4">A back-drive motor driven by an inverter or Variable Frequency Drive (VFD) automatically controls the decanter differential speed. An electronic controller monitors the current drawn by the back-drive motor, which is a direct indicator of the torque on the scroll.</p>
        <p class="text-text-light leading-relaxed mb-4">In a simple execution, any increase in the back-drive motor's current causes a proportional increase in the back-drive speed. This increased scroll speed pushes out the sludge faster, reducing the scroll's load.</p>
        <p class="text-text-light leading-relaxed mb-4">A significant increase in the scroll torque (as determined by the motor current) may trigger a temporary feed shut-off to allow the scroll to catch up with the bowl's sludge. Any further increases in the motor current (torque) trigger an automatic decanter shut-down with an 'over-torque' alarm.</p>
        <p class="text-text-light leading-relaxed">Dolphin Centrifuge decanter <a href="/industrial-centrifuge-controls/" class="text-navy font-semibold hover:text-gold transition-colors">control systems</a> feature these advanced functions for automatic scroll speed adjustment during the process.</p>
